All Classes

  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    CargoMechanism
    The subsystem that intakes, holds, lifts, and shoots cargo.
    Climb
    The subsystem that raises the robot off the ground and drives it forward onto the platform.
    Drive
    The subsystem that drives the robot around the field (the west coast drivetrain)
    ExampleSubsystem
    An example subsystem, which may be used as a template.
    HatchMechanism
    The hatch subsystem, which passively intakes hatches and actively outtakes (ejects) them.
    Main
    Do NOT add any static variables to this class, or any initialization at all.
    PressureTransducer
    Interprets the analog readings from the pressure transducer to determine PSI.
    Robot
    The VM is configured to automatically run this class, and to call the functions corresponding to each mode, as described in the IterativeRobot documentation.
    RobotMap
    The purpose of the RobotMap is to state what the parts of the robot are.
    UnoJoy
    A special kind of Joystick that is actually an Arduino Uno with firmware on it that makes it behave like a joystick.
